<paragraph id="8BE5FB4F1012FFA7FF64F9AF789F5C33" blockId="5.[136,1452,792,2086]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="B92E275D1012FFA7FF64F9AF79475249" bold="true" box="[189,265,1602,1628]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Notes:</emphasis>
Our isolate 
<collectionCode id="ED4B638A1012FFA7FE43F9AF7A4F5249" box="[410,513,1602,1628]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">KUMCC</collectionCode>
21-0467 shares similar characteristics with 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC1012FFA7FC22F9AC7CA3524E" baseAuthorityName="ARSEF" baseAuthorityYear="1139" box="[1019,1261,1601,1627]" family="Basidiobolaceae" genus="Basidiobolus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Basidiobolales" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" phylum="Zygomycota" rank="species" species="magnus">
<emphasis id="B92E275D1012FFA7FC22F9AC7CA3524E" box="[1019,1261,1601,1627]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Basidiobolus magnus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC1012FFA7FAF1F9AF7DE5524E" box="[1320,1451,1602,1627]" family="Basidiobolaceae" genus="Basidiobolus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Basidiobolales" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" phylum="Zygomycota" rank="species" species="ranarum">
<emphasis id="B92E275D1012FFA7FAF1F9AF7DE5524E" box="[1320,1451,1602,1627]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">B. ranarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having globose to subglobose, smooth, thick-walled zygospore 20–60 μm in diameter, wrapped in mycelium, with a conjugation beak (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB86BE1012FFA7FEB5F96579B452B7" author="Eidam, E." box="[364,506,1672,1698]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" pagination="181 - 251" refId="ref9970" refString="Eidam, E. (1886) Basidiobolus, eine neue Gattung der Entomophthoraeeen. Beitrage zur Biologie der Pflanzen 4: 181 - 251." type="journal article" year="1886">Eidam 1886</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB86BE1012FFA7FDDFF9657A8252B7" author="Davis, S. R. &amp; Ellis, D. H. &amp; Goldwater, P. &amp; Dimitriou, S. &amp; Byard, R." box="[518,716,1672,1698]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" pagination="225 - 230" refId="ref9631" refString="Davis, S. R., Ellis, D. H., Goldwater, P., Dimitriou, S. &amp; Byard, R. (1994) First human culture-proven australian case of entomophthoromycosis caused by Basidiobolus ranarum. Journal of Medical &amp; Veterinary Mycology 32: 225 - 230. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 02681219480000291" type="journal article" year="1994">
Davis 
<emphasis id="B92E275D1012FFA7FD96F9647AC652B7" box="[591,648,1672,1698]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">et al.</emphasis>
1994
</bibRefCitation>
). The BLASTn results show the 
<collectionCode id="ED4B638A1012FFA7FBE6F9657C2752B7" box="[1087,1129,1672,1698]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">ITS</collectionCode>
gene region highly overlaps with 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC1012FFA7FF18F94179A952D0" authority="(ARSEF 1139)" baseAuthorityName="ARSEF" baseAuthorityYear="1139" box="[193,487,1707,1733]" family="Basidiobolaceae" genus="Basidiobolus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Basidiobolales" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" phylum="Zygomycota" rank="species" species="magnus">
<emphasis id="B92E275D1012FFA7FF18F941797952D0" box="[193,311,1708,1733]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">B. magnus</emphasis>
(ARSEF 1139)
</taxonomicName>
at 99.3% (668/673 bp, 0 gap), at 99% (664/672 bp, 0 gap) similarity with 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC1012FFA7FAF3F9417DE552D0" box="[1322,1451,1708,1733]" family="Basidiobolaceae" genus="Basidiobolus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Basidiobolales" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" phylum="Zygomycota" rank="species" species="ranarum">
<emphasis id="B92E275D1012FFA7FAF3F9417DE552D0" box="[1322,1451,1708,1733]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">B. ranarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectionCode id="ED4B638A1012FFA7FF49F92378A752FD" box="[144,233,1742,1768]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14687" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14687" name="U.S. Plant, Soil and Nutrition Laboratory, USDA/ARS" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" type="Herbarium">ARSEF</collectionCode>
260), and the 
<collectionCode id="ED4B638A1012FFA7FE53F92379F152FD" box="[394,447,1742,1768]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15590" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15590" name="Louisiana State University - Herbarium" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" type="Herbarium">LSU</collectionCode>
region indicates 99.8 % similarity (1010/1012bp, 0 gap) with 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC1012FFA7FBA3F9227CB552FD" box="[1146,1275,1743,1768]" family="Basidiobolaceae" genus="Basidiobolus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Basidiobolales" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" phylum="Zygomycota" rank="species" species="ranarum">
<emphasis id="B92E275D1012FFA7FBA3F9227CB552FD" box="[1146,1275,1743,1768]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">B. ranarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectionCode id="ED4B638A1012FFA7FAD3F9237D2D52FD" box="[1290,1379,1742,1768]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14687" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14687" name="U.S. Plant, Soil and Nutrition Laboratory, USDA/ARS" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" type="Herbarium">ARSEF</collectionCode>
8303) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC1012FFA7FF60F91F797F531E" baseAuthorityName="ARSEF" baseAuthorityYear="1139" box="[185,305,1778,1803]" family="Basidiobolaceae" genus="Basidiobolus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Basidiobolales" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" phylum="Zygomycota" rank="species" species="magnus">
<emphasis id="B92E275D1012FFA7FF60F91F797F531E" box="[185,305,1778,1803]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">B. magnus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectionCode id="ED4B638A1012FFA7FE9BF91F79365319" box="[322,376,1778,1804]" country="Netherlands" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/bxq2-d2kh" name="Centraalbureau voor Schimmelcultures, Fungal and Yeast Collection" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">CBS</collectionCode>
205.64). In addition, 667 bp of the mtSSU region was 100% similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC1012FFA7FB6AF91F7D78531E" box="[1203,1334,1778,1803]" family="Basidiobolaceae" genus="Basidiobolus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Basidiobolales" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" phylum="Zygomycota" rank="species" species="ranarum">
<emphasis id="B92E275D1012FFA7FB6AF91F7D78531E" box="[1203,1334,1778,1803]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">B. ranarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(AFTOL-ID 301); unfortunately, we were unable to amplify the 
<emphasis id="B92E275D1012FFA7FCD2F8F87B0E533A" box="[779,832,1813,1839]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">rpb2</emphasis>
(7F/11aR) gene of our strain 
<collectionCode id="ED4B638A1012FFA7FB79F8F87D49533A" box="[1184,1287,1813,1839]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">KUMCC</collectionCode>
21-0467, The phylogenetic trees based on 
<collectionCode id="ED4B638A1012FFA7FE11F8D579BB5347" box="[456,501,1848,1874]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">ITS</collectionCode>
, 
<collectionCode id="ED4B638A1012FFA7FDD9F8D57A765347" box="[512,568,1848,1874]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15590" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15590" name="Louisiana State University - Herbarium" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" type="Herbarium">LSU</collectionCode>
, 
<emphasis id="B92E275D1012FFA7FD9DF8D57A365347" box="[580,632,1848,1874]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">rpb2</emphasis>
and mtSSU show our isolate clusters with 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC1012FFA7FBB9F8D47CAC5347" box="[1120,1250,1849,1874]" family="Basidiobolaceae" genus="Basidiobolus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Basidiobolales" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" phylum="Zygomycota" rank="species" species="ranarum">
<emphasis id="B92E275D1012FFA7FBB9F8D47CAC5347" box="[1120,1250,1849,1874]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">B. ranarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectionCode id="ED4B638A1012FFA7FB28F8D57D045347" box="[1265,1354,1848,1874]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14687" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14687" name="U.S. Plant, Soil and Nutrition Laboratory, USDA/ARS" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" type="Herbarium">ARSEF</collectionCode>
260 and 
<collectionCode id="ED4B638A1012FFA7FF51F8B6789E5360" box="[136,208,1883,1909]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/b0k1-wg01" name="American Type Culture Collection" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">ATCC</collectionCode>
14449) (
<figureCitation id="1361E7CA1012FFA7FEECF8B679D75360" box="[309,409,1883,1909]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1632,1654]" captionTargetBox="[202,1429,295,1594]" captionTargetId="figure-24@4.[151,1436,295,1607]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Phylogram generated from maximum likelihood analysis based on a combined LSU, ITS, rpb2 and mtSSU sequence datasets. Related sequences were taken from Gryganskyi et al. (2013), Nie et al. (2020) and Al-Hatmi et al. (2021). The 14 strains are included in the combined gene analyses; 3258 total characters including gaps (LSU: 1–1021 bp, ITS: 1022–1745 bp, rpb2: 1746–2590 bp, mtSSU: 2591–3258 bp). Tree topology of the ML analysis was similar to the BI. The matrix had distinct alignment patterns, with the final ML optimization likelihood value of -10673.579273 (ln).All free model parameters were estimated using the RAxML model, with 586 distinct alignment patterns and 21.73% undetermined characters or gaps. Estimated base frequencies were as follows:A = 0.280858, C = 0.195362, G = 0.257773, T = 0.266007, with substitution rates AC = 1.709550, AG = 4.063199, AT = 2.099405, CG = 1.130856, CT = 8.827188, GT = 1.000000. The gamma distribution shape parameter alpha = 0.109274 and the Tree-Length = 4.770478. The final average standard deviation of split frequencies at the end of total MCMC generations were calculated as 0.009712 in BI analysis. The species determined in this study are indicated in red. Bootstrap values equal to or greater than 70% (ML, left) and Bayesian posterior probabilities (BI, right) equal to or greater than 0.90 are given at the nodes. Hyphens (-) represent support values less than 70% in ML/0.90 in BI." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520355" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520355/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Figure 2</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC1012FFA7FE77F8B67AE75360" box="[430,681,1883,1909]" family="Basidiobolaceae" genus="Basidiobolus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Basidiobolales" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" phylum="Zygomycota" rank="species" species="ranarum">
<emphasis id="B92E275D1012FFA7FE77F8B67AE75360" box="[430,681,1883,1909]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Basidiobolus ranarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has also been found on frogs in 
<collectingCountry id="F34DBBDF1012FFA7FBC0F8B67C3E5360" box="[1049,1136,1883,1909]" name="Canada" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Canada</collectingCountry>
, and many infected cases in humans all over the world have been reported (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB86BE1012FFA7FD4AF8937B78538D" author="Gugnani, H. C." box="[659,822,1918,1944]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" pagination="923 - 929" refId="ref10771" refString="Gugnani, H. C. (1999) A review of zygomycosis due to Basidiobolus ranarum. European journal of epidemiology 15: 923 - 929. https: // doi. org / 10.1023 / A: 1007656818038" type="journal article" year="1999">Gugnani 1999</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB86BE1012FFA7FCE6F8937C65538D" author="Al-Hatmi, A. M. S. &amp; Balkhair, A. &amp; Al-Busaidi, I. &amp; Sandoval-Denis, M. &amp; Al-Housni, S. &amp; Ba Taher, H. &amp; Hamdan Al-Shehhi, A. &amp; Raniga, S. &amp; Shaibi, M. &amp; Al-Siyabi, T. &amp; Sybren de Hoog, G. &amp; Jacques, F. M. &amp; Al-Rawahi, A. &amp; Al-Muharrmi, Z. &amp; Al-Harrasi, A. &amp; Al-Adawi, B." box="[831,1067,1918,1944]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" pagination="653" refId="ref8300" refString="Al-Hatmi, A. M. S., Balkhair, A., Al-Busaidi, I., Sandoval-Denis, M., Al-Housni, S., Ba Taher, H., Hamdan Al-Shehhi, A., Raniga, S., Al- Shaibi, M., Al-Siyabi, T., Sybren de Hoog, G., Jacques, F. M., Al-Rawahi, A., Al-Muharrmi, Z., Al-Harrasi, A., Al-Adawi, B. (2021) Basidiobolus omanensis sp. nov. causing angioinvasive abdominal basidiobolomycosis. Journal of Fungi 7: 653. https: // doi. org / 10.3390 / jof 7080653" type="journal article" year="2021">
Al-Hatmi 
<emphasis id="B92E275D1012FFA7FC68F8927BA7538D" box="[945,1001,1918,1944]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">et al.</emphasis>
2021
</bibRefCitation>
). As morphological characteristics examined largely overlap with 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC1012FFA7FE31F84F7A2453AE" box="[488,618,1954,1979]" family="Basidiobolaceae" genus="Basidiobolus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Basidiobolales" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" phylum="Zygomycota" rank="species" species="ranarum">
<emphasis id="B92E275D1012FFA7FE31F84F7A2453AE" box="[488,618,1954,1979]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">B. ranarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, also supported by the phylogenetic evidences, our isolate is identified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC1012FFA7FF51F82879CB53CB" box="[136,389,1989,2015]" family="Basidiobolaceae" genus="Basidiobolus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Basidiobolales" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" phylum="Zygomycota" rank="species" species="ranarum">
<emphasis id="B92E275D1012FFA7FF51F82879CB53CB" box="[136,389,1989,2015]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Basidiobolus ranarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with a new country record for 
<collectingCountry id="F34DBBDF1012FFA7FD36F8287B7B53CA" box="[751,821,1989,2015]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">China</collectingCountry>
; however, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC1012FFA7FC6BF8287C7B53CB" box="[946,1077,1989,2014]" family="Basidiobolaceae" genus="Basidiobolus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Basidiobolales" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" phylum="Zygomycota" rank="species" species="ranarum">
<emphasis id="B92E275D1012FFA7FC6BF8287C7B53CB" box="[946,1077,1989,2014]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">B. ranarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has previously been reported on wall gecko and house gecko faeces (
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC1012FFA7FDC3F8057AA75C17" box="[538,745,2024,2050]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Hemidactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B92E275D1012FFA7FDC3F8057AFA5C17" box="[538,692,2024,2050]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Hemidactylus</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB86BE1012FFA7FD26F8057C5C5C17" author="Gugnani, H. C. &amp; Okafor, J. I." box="[767,1042,2024,2050]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" pagination="260 - 268" refId="ref10811" refString="Gugnani, H. C. &amp; Okafor, J. I. (1980) Mycotic flora of the intestine and other internal organs of certain reptiles and amphibians with special reference to characterization of Basidiobolus isolates. Mycosen 23: 260 - 268. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1439 - 0507.1980. tb 02605. x" type="journal article" year="1980">Gugnani &amp; Okafor 1980</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB86BE1012FFA7FBC5F8057CF05C17" author="Gugnani, H. C." box="[1052,1214,2024,2050]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" pagination="923 - 929" refId="ref10771" refString="Gugnani, H. C. (1999) A review of zygomycosis due to Basidiobolus ranarum. European journal of epidemiology 15: 923 - 929. https: // doi. org / 10.1023 / A: 1007656818038" type="journal article" year="1999">Gugnani 1999</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB86BE1012FFA7FB1EF805788B5C33" author="Claussen, M. &amp; Schmidt, S." pageId="5" pageNumber="42" pagination="298 - 305" refId="ref9387" refString="Claussen, M. &amp; Schmidt, S. (2019) First-time isolation and quantification of Basidiobolus spp. from reptile faeces in KwaZulu-Natal (South Africa) using selective media. Mycoses 62: 298 - 305. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / myc. 12868" type="journal article" year="2019">Claussen &amp; Schmidt 2019</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
